&gt; 
&gt; HTML has a type attribute for hyperlink elements such as script, style,
&gt; anchor - it is used to advise on the media type that should be
&gt; expected;
&gt; but it is not, for some reason, intended to affect the Accept header
&gt; for
&gt; requests to the corresponding URI.
&gt; 
&gt; It seems to make sense to me that it should, so I filed a bug report.
&gt; 
&gt; Any thoughts?
&gt; 
&gt; http://www.w3.org/Bugs/Public/show_bug.cgi?id=7697
&gt; 
&gt; Description:
&gt; 
