&gt; elements&gt;
&gt; The type attribute should ammend the Accept header accordingly. HTTP
&gt; spec is in
&gt; accordance with the rules here, in terms of the Accept header being
&gt; non-authorative. script and style elements already ammend accept header
&gt; (in
&gt; firefox) but not for other link elements. This behaviour would be
&gt; valuable for
&gt; enabling HTML powered applications which leverage HTTP conneg.
